Lądek  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Bisztynek, within Bartoszyce County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Bisztynek,  south of Bartoszyce, and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
Before 1772 the area was part of Kingdom of Poland, 1772–1945 Prussia and Germany (East Prussia).
